step_data.thought:
I'm now on the Orders page in the Magento Admin panel. Looking at the current state, I can see that filters have already been applied to show orders from March 1, 2025 to March 31, 2025, which is essentially showing orders from the last month (March 2025). This is evident from the 'Active filters' section which shows 'Purchase Date: 3/01/2025 - 3/31/2025'.

The table below shows 5 orders that match this filter criteria, all with dates in March 2025. Since the filters for viewing orders from the last month are already applied, the goal has been accomplished.

I should inform the user that the filters for the last month are already applied and the orders are currently being displayed.
step_data.action: stop('The filters for viewing orders from the last month (March 1-31, 2025) are already applied. The page is currently displaying 5 orders that match this criteria, all with purchase dates in March 2025.')
